quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  18,1,"PRAISE be to God, who hath sent down the Book to his servant, and hath not made it tortuous"
  18,2,"But direct; that it may warn of a grievous woe from him, and announce to the faithful who do the things that are right, that a goodly reward"
  18,3,"wherein they shall abide for ever, awaiteth them"
  18,4,"And that it may warn those who say, \"God hath begotten a Son"
  18,5,No knowledge of this have either they or their fathers! A grievous saying to come out of their mouths! They speak no other than a lie
  18,6,"And haply, if they believe not in this new revelation, thou wilt slay thyself, on their very footsteps, out of vexation"
  18,7,"Verily, we have made all that is on earth as its adornment, that we might make trial who among mankind would excel in works"
  18,8,But we are surely about to reduce all that is thereon to dust
  18,9,Hast thou reflected that the Inmates of THE CAVE and of Al Rakim were on our wondrous signs
  18,10,"When the youths betook them to the cave they said, \"O our Lord! grant us mercy from before thee, and order for us our affair aright"
  18,11,Then struck we upon their ears with deafness in the cave for many a year
  18,12,Then we awaked them that we might know which of the two parties could best reckon the space of their abiding